    <center><h1>CNS Home Assaingnment</h1><h3>KLUNIVERSITY</h3></center>
    <h5>  1.</h5> Given 10 bit key 1010101010 generate the two keys K1 & K2 using S-DES algorithm using the following functions P10 (5 3 8 10 1 6 9 2 4 7) and P8 (9 4 5 8 2 6 7 10). Encrypt the following plaintext 11110000 using the functions IP (2 6 3 1 4 8 5 7), E (3 4 1 2 4 3 2 1) S0 = {(1 0 3 2) (3 2 1 0) (0 2 1 3) (3 1 3 2)} S1 = {(0 1 2 3) (2 0 1 3) (3 0 1 0) (2 1 0 3)} and P4 (2 4 3 1)
[General Subject Question on DES algorithm – All Reference Books)

&NewLine;<h5>2.</h5> a. What are Different nonlinear components and linear components involved in DES? Explain.
b. How many “XOR” Operations are used in DES Cipher? Demonstrate the number against each round of DES Algorithm
[Atul Kahate, 2003, P. No. 77-82] &
[Behrouz A Forouzan, “Cryptography and Network Security”, 2nd Ed, 2010, P. No. 172]

&NewLine;<h5>3.</h5> a. Consider a plaintext message “I AM A HACKER“, Encrypt it with the help of the following algorithm:
(a) Replace each alphabet with its equivalent 7-bit ASCII code.
(b) Add a 0 bit as the leftmost bit to make each of the above bit pattern 8 positions long.
(c) Swap the first four bits with the last four bits for each alphabet.
(d) Write the hexadecimal equivalent of every four bits.
[Atul Kahate, 2003, P. No. 62]
b. The encryption Key in a columnar transposition cipher is (3 2 6 1 5 4). Find decryption key.
[Behrouz A Forouzan, “Cryptography and Network Security”, 2nd Ed, 2010, P. No. 81]

&NewLine;<h5>4.</h5> a. Using Vigenere cipher Encrypt the word “GIVE EXPLANATION BY MONDAY MORNING” using the key “leg”.
b. Encrypt the plain text message “the key is hidden under the door pad” using playfair cipher from the key “GUIDANCE”.
[Behrouz A Forouzan, “Cryptography and Network Security”, 2nd Ed, 2010, P. No. 80]

&NewLine;<h5>5.</h5> a. Why do you think mixing transformation (Mix Columns) is not needed in DES, but is needed in AES? Justify your answer with example.
b. Which of the four transformations defined for AES change the contents of bytes? Which does not change the contents of the bytes; Give an Example to justify your answer?
[Behrouz A Forouzan, “Cryptography and Network Security”, 2nd Ed, 2010, P. No. 201]

